# Model Notes – Neural Style Transfer

## Overview

This project implements neural style transfer using a pretrained VGG19 network.

The goal is to generate an image that preserves the content of one image while adopting the artistic style of another.

## Architecture

The method uses a pretrained VGG19 convolutional network to extract features from images.

Two types of representations are used:

- Content representations
- Style representations

## Content Loss

Content loss measures the difference between the content features of the generated image and the original content image.

## Style Loss

Style is represented using Gram matrices computed from feature maps.

These matrices capture correlations between feature channels.

## Optimization

The generated image is initialized as noise and iteratively optimized using gradient descent.

The objective minimizes:

Total Loss = Content Loss + Style Loss